[{'title': 'ISC Stormcast For Monday, June 22nd, 2026 https://isc.sans.edu/podcastdetail/9980, (Mon, Jun 22nd)', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 22 Jun 2026 02:00:02 GMT', 'source': 'https://isc.sans.edu/diary/rss/33092', 'source_type': "['operational', 'strategical']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {}}, {'title': 'AryStinger botnet infected thousands of D-Link routers worldwide', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 10:14:22 -0400', 'source': 'https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/arystinger-botnet-infected-thousands-of-d-link-routers-worldwide/', 'source_type': "['operational', 'vulnerabilities']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["Researchers at Qianxin's XLab threat intelligence team say that the malware converts infected devices into remotely controlled “executors” that can perform scanning, proxying, tunneling, command execution, and other activities on behalf of the attacker.", '“With this distributed-like design, the attacker can efficiently complete the early "footprinting" activities, thereby providing strong assurance for the smoothness and success rate of subsequent intrusion operations.”', 'Apart from using compromised routers as a springboard for malicious operations, XLab warns that the malware can also tamper with DNS settings, hijacking the user’s browsing, and silently monitor and potentially steal all inbound and outbound network traffic.', 'XLab researchers found two variants of the AryStinger malware: a C-based version targeting mostly outdated routers, and a Go-based one that focuses on NAS systems, but currently with a far more limited reach.', 'The NAS version is the most advanced of the two, featuring additional capabilities such as IP and DNS scanning, command execution, payload execution, and internal network reconnaissance through the integration of open-source penetration testing tools.', "The researchers noted that AryStinger's distributed DNS-scanning infrastructure could potentially be repurposed to generate large volumes of DNS queries against resolvers, although they did not observe any such attacks.", 'However, there are some limitations to using source code instead of compiled binaries, as compilation requires language runtimes on the host, and the process as a whole introduces noise that can break stealth.', 'Owners of end-of-life (EoL) routers should replace them with new, actively supported models, apply the latest available firmware updates, change the default administrator account password, and disable remote management panels.'], 'observables': {'vulnerability': ['CVE-2013-3307', 'CVE-2016-5681', 'CVE-2025-11837']}}, {'title': 'SECURITY AFFAIRS MALWARE NEWSLETTER ROUND 102', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 20:15:22 +0000', 'source': 'https://securityaffairs.com/193960/security/security-affairs-malware-newsletter-round-102.html', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['pierluigi.paganini@securityaffairs.co']}}, {'title': 'Security Affairs newsletter Round 582 by Pierluigi Paganini – INTERNATIONAL EDITION', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 17:19:49 +0000', 'source': 'https://securityaffairs.com/193953/uncategorized/security-affairs-newsletter-round-582-by-pierluigi-paganini-international-edition.html', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['pierluigi.paganini@securityaffairs.co'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-20262', 'CVE-2026-0257']}}, {'title': 'Let’s test Tesla.com Vs. Hecate deep paint OSINT tool #tesla #osint #hacker #redteaming #bugbounty', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 22 Jun 2026 01:33:11 +0000', 'source': 'https://www.reddit.com/r/blueteamsec/comments/1uc6p36/lets_test_teslacom_vs_hecate_deep_paint_osint/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Si tu choisis « Refuser les cookies optionnels », nous n’utiliserons pas de cookies pour ces utilisations supplémentaires. Tu peux mettre à jour tes préférences en matière de cookies dans tes paramètres.'], 'observables': {}}, {'title': 'I put a small SSH honeypot on the internet. The internet found it fast.', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 22 Jun 2026 01:33:11 +0000', 'source': 'https://www.reddit.com/r/blueteamsec/comments/1uc4c0x/i_put_a_small_ssh_honeypot_on_the_internet_the/', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["Ce n'est pas un produit ou quelque chose de commercial. C'est juste un projet de laboratoire personnel pour m'améliorer dans la collecte de télémétrie de sécurité désordonnée et la transformer en quelque chose d'utile.", "J'ai aussi ajouté Dionaea, Honeytrap, des chemins d'attrait Nginx, et Suricata pour pouvoir voir plus que juste SSH. Dionaea a capturé l'activité de service/protocole à travers MySQL, SMB, MSSQL, FTP, TFTP, et SIP. La plupart de cela n'est que des preuves de protocole/session, pas de malware, mais une DLL similaire à un PE Windows a été capturée pour une analyse statique hors ligne.", "J'ai ajouté un deuxième hôte leurre qui agit comme une fausse API interne. Le premier honeypot a des credentials plantés, de faux tokens API, et des fichiers de suivi. La deuxième machine enregistre la validation des tokens, les fausses frappes d'API, les manipulations de fichiers, et les tentatives de réutilisation de credentials.", "Je sais que les honeypots ne sont pas nouveaux, mais cela a été un bon rappel que le travail de sécurité pratique ne porte pas toujours sur des zéro-days exotiques. Parfois, il s'agit de surveiller en toute sécurité le bruit constant en arrière-plan et de construire suffisamment de pipeline autour de cela pour poser de meilleures questions.", 'Si tu choisis « Refuser les cookies optionnels », nous n’utiliserons pas de cookies pour ces utilisations supplémentaires. Tu peux mettre à jour tes préférences en matière de cookies dans tes paramètres.'], 'observables': {}}, {'title': 'Amazon AWS: 55 CVEs, 98% unpatched, Trust Score C. 18 critical/high flaws. Top weaknesses: CWE-89 (SQL injection) & CWE-78 (OS command injection). Cloud dominance ≠ secure defaults. Fix your attack surface. #AWS #cybersecurity #infosechttps://www.valtersit.com/vendors/amazon/', 'publication_date': 'Mon, 22 Jun 2026 01:03:19 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@hugovalters/116790838046459927', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['valtersit.com'], 'email-addr': ['hugovalters@mastodon.social'], 'url': ['http://www.valtersit.com']}}, {'title': "Several C2 (Command and Control) use case, I didn't realize Counter Strike can also be a C2.Credit: @hackers_arise https://hackers-arise.com/living-off-the-land-creative-c2-and-data-exfiltration-options/#cybersecurity #infosec #c2 #commandandcontrolservers", 'publication_date': 'Mon, 22 Jun 2026 00:04:28 +0000', 'source': 'https://infosec.exchange/@AmmarSpaces/116790714284083216', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'artifact': [], 'autonomous-system': [], 'directory': [], 'domain-name': [], 'email-addr': [], 'email-message': [], 'file': [], 'ipv4-addr': [], 'ipv6-addr': [], 'mac-addr': [], 'mutex': [], 'network-traffic': [], 'process': [], 'software': [], 'url': [], 'user-account': [], 'windows-registry-key': [], 'x509-certificate': [], 'vulnerability': [], 'mitre': []}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-11551 - Critical privilege escalation in Branda WordPress plugin. Unauthenticated account takeover via improper password reset validation. CVSS 9.8. No patch available. Disable immediately. #CVE #WordPress #infosechttps://www.valtersit.com/cve/CVE-2026-11551/', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 23:05:47 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@hugovalters/116790595561097570', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['valtersit.com'], 'email-addr': ['hugovalters@mastodon.social'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-11551']}}, {'title': "I have seen my first Google QR code I couldn't avoid. You scan the code, it sends you to a page on your phone that has you send a message to a number. In the bottom corner they claim it isn't used to link your phone. (Bart)(and I am very grateful I can buy SIM cards off the shelf, for now). It's extra moronic to do this amid the prevalence of ClickFix but that has been discussed to death.#privacy #infosec", 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 23:05:47 +0000', 'source': 'https://infosec.exchange/@sharkfie/116790580361949823', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["I have seen my first Google QR code I couldn't avoid. You scan the code, it sends you to a page on your phone that has you send a message to a number. In the bottom corner they claim it isn't used to link your phone. (Bart)"], 'observables': {}}, {'title': "@mysk don't believe for a second WhatsApp ever had E2EE at all.Same for Signal, Telegram, Threema, Matrix, etc…If you can't self-host it's servers,reproduceably build servers & clientsdev. your own servers and clients w/ feature parity.as well as use it without self-doxxing aka. needing a Phone Number,it's insecure!Because Phone Numbers are intrinsically insecure, as they can always be linked to a device [Number->SIM->ICCID->IMEI) / client (SIP uses UDP = no Tor!) and thus trivially connected by circumstances to a person!So go with PGP/MIME ( @delta & @thunderbird and/or XMPP+OMEMO ( @gajim and/or @monocles  ) over @torproject!VPNs are snitchesIf nachash wouldn't touch it, why should you?#WhatsApp #E2EE #Signal #Threema #Telegram #Matrix #SelfHosting #ReproduceableBuilds #Server #Client #OpenSource #OpenStandards #SelfDoxxing #KYC #ID #PhoneNumber #SIM #IMEI #Privacy #UDP #Tor #OpSec #InfoSec #ComSec #ITsec #OMEMO #PGP", 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 23:05:47 +0000', 'source': 'https://tech.lgbt/@Netzblockierer/116790521883292876', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['github.com', 'web.archive.org'], 'email-addr': ['Netzblockierer@tech.lgbt'], 'url': ['https://blog.cryptographyengineering.com/2026/02/02/whatsapp-encryption-a-lawsuit-and-a-lot-of-noise/', 'https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=Naq5IojVoNsALTHide', 'https://t.co/Q2aOQJkG4g”#WhatsApp#E2EE#Signal…and']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-12806 - Edimax BR-6478AC V2 POST Request formWlSiteSurvey buffer overflow', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 19:30:08 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-12806', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['A vulnerability has been found in Edimax BR-6478AC V2 1.23. The impacted element is the function formWlSiteSurvey of the file /goform/formWlSiteSurvey of the component POST Request Handler. The manipulation of the argument selSSID leads to buffer overflow. It is possible to initiate the attack remotely. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used. The vendor was contacted early about this disclosure but did not respond in any way.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-12806vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['cna@vuldb.com'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-12806']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-56397 - SiYuan - Remote Code Execution via Malicious Bazaar Package Metadata and README', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 13:27:04 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-56397', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["SiYuan before v3.6.1 fails to sanitize package metadata and README content in the Bazaar marketplace, allowing malicious package authors to inject arbitrary HTML and JavaScript. Attackers can achieve remote code execution on any user browsing the Bazaar by embedding XSS payloads in package displayName, description, or README fields, exploiting Electron's nodeIntegration setting to execute OS commands.", 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-56397vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-56397']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-56396 - phpMyFAQ - Privilege Escalation via Missing Authorization in editUser() and updateUserRights()', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 13:27:03 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-56396', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['phpMyFAQ before 4.1.4 contains missing authorization vulnerabilities in editUser() and updateUserRights() endpoints that allow authenticated administrators to escalate privileges. Non-SuperAdmin users with edit_user permission can set is_superadmin flag or grant arbitrary rights to escalate to SuperAdmin access.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-56396vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-56396']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-56395 - SiYuan - Remote Code Execution via Malicious Bazaar Package Metadata and README', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 13:27:03 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-56395', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["SiYuan before v3.6.1 fails to sanitize package metadata and README content in the Bazaar marketplace, allowing malicious package authors to inject arbitrary HTML and JavaScript. Attackers can achieve remote code execution on any user browsing the Bazaar by embedding XSS payloads in package displayName, description, or README fields, exploiting Electron's nodeIntegration setting to execute OS commands.", 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-56395vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-56395']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-56382 - Craft CMS - Remote Code Execution via Missing Config Sanitization in FieldsController', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 13:26:58 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-56382', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["Craft CMS (composer package craftcms/cms) versions >= 5.5.0 and <= 5.9.13 contain a remote code execution vulnerability in the FieldsController::actionRenderCardPreview() method, which passes the fieldLayoutConfig POST parameter directly to Fields::createLayout() without calling Component::cleanseConfig(). An authenticated admin user can inject Yii2 event handlers (e.g., 'on init' keys) via the fieldLayoutConfig parameter to execute arbitrary PHP code and disclose sensitive information (such as environment variables containing database credentials and CRAFT_SECURITY_KEY). The issue is fixed in version 5.9.14.", 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-56382vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-56382']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-56265 - Crawl4AI - Authentication Bypass via Hardcoded JWT Signing Key', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 13:26:54 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-56265', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Crawl4AI before 0.8.7 contains an authentication bypass vulnerability due to a hardcoded default JWT signing key in the Docker API server. Attackers who know the default key can forge valid authentication tokens for any user, bypassing authentication and gaining full access to protected functionality.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-56265vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-56265']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-56253 - Capgo - Unauthenticated Organization Member Email Disclosure via get_org_members RPC', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 13:26:54 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-56253', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Capgo before 12.128.2 contains an improper access control vulnerability in the public.get_org_members RPC function that allows unauthenticated attackers to enumerate organization members. Attackers can invoke the endpoint using only the public sb_publishable_* key and an organization UUID to retrieve sensitive member information including email addresses, user IDs, roles, and pending invitations.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-56253vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).'], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-56253']}}, {'title': 'Brazil’s Civil Defense suffers a cyberattack on its official alert network', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 19:13:49 +0000', 'source': 'https://databreaches.net/2026/06/21/brazils-civil-defense-suffers-a-cyberattack-on-its-official-alert-network/?pk_campaign=feed&pk_kwd=brazils-civil-defense-suffers-a-cyberattack-on-its-official-alert-network', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['databreaches.net']}}, {'title': 'Two Data Breaches Didn’t Sink Novo Nordisk’s Stock. Why Not?', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 16:27:55 +0000', 'source': 'https://databreaches.net/2026/06/21/two-data-breaches-didnt-sink-novo-nordisks-stock-why-not/?pk_campaign=feed&pk_kwd=two-data-breaches-didnt-sink-novo-nordisks-stock-why-not', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['databreaches.net']}}, {'title': 'Klue OAuth breach victim list grows as Icarus hackers claim attack', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 21 Jun 2026 15:01:03 +0000', 'source': 'https://databreaches.net/2026/06/21/klue-oauth-b